<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 9. Pseudozeuxo fischeri sp. nov. Paratype, female dissected (MNRJ 29869). A Dorsal view; B enlargement of pleon and pleotelson. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." , "Figure 8. Digital image of Pseudozeuxo fischeri sp. nov. paratype female (MNRJ 29869) and allotype male lateral (MNRJ 29868). Female, TL 1.2 mm; Male, TL 1.0 mm. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." , "Figure 13. Geographic distribution of Apseudomorpha brasiliensis sp. nov. (circle) and Pseudozeuxo fischeri sp. nov. (square) on the study area. A-C Areias Negras Beach, Rio das Ostras. A General view of Areias Negras Beach; B view of the rocky shore eulittoral site; C view of the quadrat sample and seaweed cover; D-F Santana Archipelago, Macae; D General view of Santana Archipelago; E view of the rocky shore eulittoral site; F view of the quadrat sample and seaweed cover. Program: QGIS 2.16.3 SRC: EPS 4326 WGS 84." , "Figure 12. Pseudozeuxo fischeri sp. nov. Paratype, female dissected (MNRJ 29869). A Pereopod- 4 with oostegite; B-C pereopods 5 - 6; D pleopod; E uropod. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." , "Figure 11. Pseudozeuxo fischeri sp. nov. Paratype, female dissected (MNRJ 29869). A Cheliped; B-D pereopods 1 - 3 with oostegites. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." , "Figure 10. Pseudozeuxo fischeri sp. nov. Paratype, female dissected (MNRJ 29869). A Antennule; B antenna; C labrum; D left mandible; E right mandible; F maxillule; G maxilla; H labium; I maxilliped. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/477275" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/477278" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/477280" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/477279" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/477276" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/477277" .

